# Git tutorial

## 1. Create repositopry
- go to [github.com](https://github.com)
- click **new repository**
- name it
- click **create repository**

## 2. Clone repository

using the repository link`

`
git clone https://github.com/username/repo-name.git
cd repo-name
`

## 3. Open in vsc
`
code .
`

## 4. Add a file

`
touch file.txt
`

`
git add file.txt
`

`
git commit -m "Add file"
`

`
git push
`

## 5. Operations
### - updating
`
git add .
`

`
git commit -m "Update file"
`

`
git push
`

### - removing 
`
git rm file.txt
`

`
git commit -m "Remove file"
`

`
git push
`

### - checking status
`
git status
`